Among the nominees with ties to Southern California was Estonian composer Arvo Pärt and his Symphony No. 4 "Los Angeles", a work commissioned through the Los Angeles Philharmonic and debuted at the Walt Disney Concert Hall in 2009.
Los Angeles-based composer Avner Dorman and his Mandolin Concerto are also up for an award.
Nominations in classical music are divided into 13 categories, which include orchestral, opera, choral and solo recordings.
