"I wrote it using Middle Eastern tones and many North African rhythms", Dorman said in a telephone interview.
Conductor Pierre Boulez, 85, has received a nomination in the category of orchestral performance for his conducting of the Chicago Symphony in the recording of Stravinsky's works.
Among the instrumental soloists who received the nomination are pianists Nelson Freire and Marc-André Hamelin; organist Paul Jacobs; violinist Julia Fischer; and harpist Sarah Schuster Ericsson.
This year, only women were nominated for the soloist position, including Anne Sofie Von Otter, Cecilia Bartoli, Lucia Duchon, Vivica Genaux and Measha Brueggergosman.
In the classical transition category, soprano Jessie Norman was nominated for her recording of "Roots - My Life, My Song".
