In a surprise victory in President Obama's campaign to secure nuclear material around the world, the Belarusian government announced Wednesday that it would give up its stockpile of highly enriched uranium, a critical component of nuclear weapons.
The agreement was announced in a joint statement issued after the Security Summit of Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton and Belarusian Foreign Minister Sergei Martynov.
The U.S. government has been trying for years to convince Belarus to give up its highly enriched uranium, and it seemed to hit a rock bottom last spring.
