That set the stage for Wednesday's agreement to remove the rest of the material - about £500, according to an official who spoke on condition of anonymity because it is a sensitive matter.
The agreement turned out to be one of the most important outcomes of Obama's 47th National Nuclear Security Summit in April, which excluded Belarus.
